Hi @patrikx3 I'm not 100% sure on what you're trying to do exactly, but it sounds like a pattern for doing granular auth restrictions per route. If that is right, one pattern you can try is to use a middleware pattern to skip, for example:
```js
// 1. Let's assume that you have a middleware that looks up a user's access level
app.use((req, res, next) => {
   req.user.accessLevel = 'public'
})

// 2. Then you could make an access level checker
function requireAccessLevel(level) {
  return (req, res, next) => {
    if (req.user && req.user.accessLevel === level) next()
    else next('route')
