Hi @m31271n 
in  my opinion you should place middeware where they are useful.  
In general middleware take care to process http request and response so if you reduce the number of used middleware you should increase performance.
In express you have three level to place middleware:
- Main Application
- Sub Applications 
- Routes

``` javascript
'use strict';
const express = require('express');
const app = express();

// Common midleware in the app
app.use(function middlewareApp(req, res, next) {
  // Process req and res ...
  next();
});

const mySubApp1 = express.Router();

// Common middleware for the sub apps
mySubApp1.use(function middlewareSubApp1(req, res, next) {
  // Process req and res ...
  next();
});


mySubApp1.get('/my-route1/',
  // Middleware for the route
